#   Spot: structural code search, grep, regex, diff, merge

Spot is the search dog: its purview is structural code search, grep, regex, replace, and token-level diff/merge, and it owns the `NNNNN.spot.idx` trigram and symbol index runs under `.be/`. The goal is instant search plus token-granular diff and merge, all syntax-highlighted. The method: tokenize source by file extension, build the indexes, seek candidates by trigram, then match by flat token pattern (SPOT), substring (grep), or a Thompson NFA (regex); diff and merge run LCS over token streams.

 -  Indexing tokenizes per extension and writes trigram + symbol runs to `.be/*.idx`; `--fork N` stripes files across N workers.
 -  A per-blob memo (blob hashlet â†’ path hashlet) skips unchanged blobs, reindexes a changed path (catches renames).
 -  SPOT and grep share trigram candidate filtering, then run token-pattern matching (SPOT) or substring over all leaves (grep).
 -  Regex pulls literal runs of 3+ chars for trigram filtering (Russ Cox), so the index still speeds patterns with literals.
 -  Diff and merge tokenize both files, run LCS over the token streams, and emit highlighted hunks with function headers.

##  API

Spot follows the [Dog] three-call contract; the CAPO layer carries the index and the search/index primitives the verbs dispatch to.

 -  `SPOTOpen` / `SPOTOpenBranch` / `SPOTClose` â€” open the index, add a branch's shard, then close.
 -  `SPOTExec(state, cli)` â€” dispatch a parsed verb plus URIs against the open index.
 -  `SPOTIndexFromTips` â€” incremental reindex walking the invoking URI's tips; pulls blobs from [Keeper].
 -  `CAPOIndexFile` / `CAPOIndexBlob` â€” tokenize and index one file or one blob into a run.
 -  `CAPOSpot` â€” structural snippet search with token/block placeholders.
 -  `CAPOGrep` / `CAPOPcreGrep` â€” indexed substring search and Thompson-NFA regex search.
 -  `SPOTReplace` â€” structural search-and-replace over matched token spans.
 -  `CAPOTrigramFilter` â€” narrow the candidate file set by trigram before matching; `CAPOCompact` merges runs.

##  CLI

The `spot` CLI is the multitool surface â€” cat, search, replace, diff, merge, and indexing â€” selectable by flag.

 -  `spot file.c` is highlighted cat; bare `spot` is an incremental update; `spot --fork N` reindexes on N cores.
 -  `spot -s 'snippet' .c` snippet-searches, `-r 'repl'` rewrites; `-g TODO .c` greps; `-p 'regex' .c` regex-greps.
 -  `spot --diff old new` token-diffs; `spot --merge base ours theirs -o out` 3-way merges; `--gitdiff`/`--hook` wire git.
 -  Trailing `.ext` args are extension filters (required for `-s`, optional for `-g`): `.c` matches `**/*.c` and `**/*.h`.

##  Snippet search (SPOT)

`-s` matches structurally, not textually, so whitespace and formatting differences are ignored; placeholders bind tokens, and `-r` rewrites them.

 -  Lowercase `a`â€“`z` bind one token (`ok64 o = OK;` also matches `ok64 ret = OK;`); uppercase `A`â€“`Z` match any block.
 -  Two spaces skip any token sequence; `-r` rewrites: `spot -s 'TOK_VAL(A,B,C,D)' -r 'tok32Val(A,B,C,D)' .c .h`.
 -  Results are syntax-highlighted with context lines and a function-header hunk title per match.

##  Git integration

Spot plugs into git as a diff and merge driver and a post-commit indexing hook, via `.gitattributes` and `git config`.

 -  Git drivers: `git config diff.spot.command "spot --gitdiff"` and a `merge.spot.driver` of `spot --merge %O %A %B -o %A`.
 -  `.gitattributes`: `*.c diff=spot merge=spot` routes C files through spot's token-level diff and merge.
 -  A post-commit `spot --hook` keeps the index incremental; `--hook` is the same as bare `spot`.

